radiographic_examinations.findings: No evidence of fibrosis; normal perfusion and viability; increased trabeculations in the RV apex and in the lateral wall and apex of the LV; no wall-motion abnormalities or abrupt transition in the thickness of compacted myocardium.

LV ejection fraction of 66% with biventricular hypertrophy; LV concentric hypertrophy, most notable at the posterior and lateral walls of the apex measuring 1.7 cm; LV basal septum measuring 1.3 cm; LV basal posterior wall measuring 1.1 cm; moderate chordal systolic anterior motion; no resting LVOT gradient; no provokable LVOT obstruction.
